latestPosts.caption:
When John Whitmire ran for mayor, he pledged to cut down the time it takes to get a residential building permit in Houston.

🛠️ Starting Monday, we’re launching the 30-Day Residential Permitting Pilot Program. It is a major step toward making it faster and easier to build in our city.

This pilot, led by the Houston Permitting Center, will test a more efficient and transparent process to issue residential permits in 30 business days or less.

This is part of a broader effort to:
 •Streamline development
 •Eliminate costly delays
 •Modernize City operations
 •Restore confidence in local government

Stay tuned for more details!

Go behind the scenes at Eleanor Tinsley Park with Mayor Whitmire and the @coh_mayors_events as they gear up for Houston’s official Fourth of July celebration, Freedom Over Texas.

Live music, family fun and a fireworks finale you won’t forget.

SPARK YOUR FREEDOM WITH FREEDOM OVER TEXAS 2025! 🎇🤩

Houston, get ready! 🎉 Head over to Eleanor Tinsley Park for the 2025 Freedom Over Texas – the city’s biggest Fourth of July celebration 🇺🇸

Join us for six hours of non-stop fun including:
🎶 Live music performances for every vibe 🎯 Family-friendly games & activities 🍔 Delicious eats and refreshing drinks 🎆 A breathtaking fireworks show lighting up #DowntownHouston

Don’t miss it! ⬇️ 📅 Friday, July 4, 2025 🕓 Starts at 4 PM 📍 Eleanor Tinsley Park | 3600 Allen Pkwy

Want more info? Comment “Firework” in the comments and we’ll light up your inbox! 💥

Bring your crew, your picnic blanket, and your Texas pride – and let’s celebrate America’s birthday in true H-Town style! 🤠🇺🇸

latestPosts.caption:
We had a successful initiative for public safety in Houston over the weekend. The multi-agency effort focused on cracking down on road rage, speeding, and reckless driving.
It worked!
⤵️
27 suspects arrested
6 DWI arrests
122 traffic citations 
4 weapons recovered 

@houstonmayor Whitmire thanks @houstonpolice, TX DPS, Houston METRO police, Precinct 5 Constable Allbritton, and the Harris County Sheriff’s Office for collaborating on this major traffic safety enforcement along I-10 & Westheimer.

In observance of Independence Day, there will be no City Council public session or agenda meeting this week.

We wish you a happy and safe July 4th! 🎆

For more updates, please visit the City of Houston website: https://houstontx.gov/index.html

latestPosts.caption:
Mayor Whitmire had the honor of welcoming Ambassador Suriya Chindawongse of Thailand to the U.S. in Houston.

They met at MaKiin, a local Thai restaurant that provided an authentic Thai dining experience and enjoyed a  meaningful discussion about 
opportunities to strengthen cultural and economic ties between Houston and Thailand

They were Joined by Thai Honorary Consul-General Charles Foster and members of the Royal Thai Embassy.

#thailand #diplomacy #houstontx
